gw.api.builder

Class JobBuilder<B extends JobBuilder<B>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<PolicyPeriod,B>
      • gw.api.builder.JobBuilder<B>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueGenerator<PolicyPeriod>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NonSubmissionJobBuilder, SubmissionBuilderBase

    public abstract class JobBuilder<B extends JobBuilder<B>>
extends DataBuilder<PolicyPeriod,B>
    Abstract superclass for builders which construct Jobs. This builder supports many properties that are shared by all job types. "JobBuilder" is a little bit of a misnomer, because the object created by the builder will actually be a PolicyPeriod. The period created by a JobBuilder subclass will be associated with a Job of the desired type.

    The general model for a DataBuilder is a class which holds onto a copy of the desired state, and registers populators which will copy the data into the object as it is being built. This class follows that model closely: it sets up several populators by default (in order to get things built in the proper order), and if certain properties are requested, it will register additional populators on demand in order to set those properties. Subclass implementors will need to take care to order their own populators correctly, so that things get done in the desired order.

    The properties specially handled by JobBuilder, and the priority number associated with each of them, is as follows. These are listed in order of priority, but within any single priority group the group members will be executed in the order they were created. Other properties handled by JobBuilder can be assumed to be done at DEFAULT_ORDER.

    <
    PropertyTypePriority number
    PolicyLocationPolicyLocationBuilderDEFAULT_ORDER
    PolicyContactRole/td>PolicyContactRoleBuilderDEFAULT_ORDER
    UWIssueUWIssueBuilderDEFAULT_ORDER
    PolicyLinePolicyLineBuilderLINEBUILDER_PRIORITY
    EffectiveDatedFieldsEffectiveDatedFieldsBuilderPOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_0
    PeriodStartDatePOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_1
    PeriodEndDatePOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_1
    PrimaryPolicyLocationPolicyLocationBuilderPOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_1
    FinalAuditOptionFinalAuditOptionPOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_1
    JobNumberStringsee subclasses
    EffectiveDateDatesee subclasses
    TermTypeTermTypesee subclasses
    ReportingPatternCodeStringsee subclasses
    PaymentPlanIDStringsee subclasses
    ProductProductsee subclasses

    JobUserRoleAssignmentUser,UserRolePOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_2
    PolicyUserRoleAssignmentUser,UserRolePOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_2
    JobCloseDateDatePOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_3
    UserAssignmentUserPOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_3
    GroupAssignmentGroupPOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_3
    NextRenewalCheckDateDatePOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_3
    NextArchiveCheckDateDatePOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_3
    JobDescriptionStringPOSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_3
    POSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_2 is frequently used by JobBuilder subclasses, although they are free to use any priority they wish. In addition, there are some "cleanup" populators for territory codes. These run after the line builders, at LINEBUILDER_PRIORITY + 1 and LINEBUILDER_PRIORITY + 2.

      • JobBuilder

        public JobBuilder()
        Create a JobBuilder. The default values set by this constructor, and the way to change them, are:
        FeatureDefaultMethod to change
        Effective DateTodaywithEffectiveDate(Date)
        Product Code"BusinessOwners"withProduct(String)
        Skip ValidationtruewithValidation()
        Skip UWIssue EvaluationtruewithUWIssueEvaluation()
        Fill Blank Territory Codes*withTerritoryCodesLeftBlank()
        * blank territory codes will be filled in only if what is being built is a submission.
        (What is actually checked is this instanceof SubmissionBuilderBase.) The flags for Validation and UWIssue evaluation are consulted when quoting and binding periods.
